6 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
7 That Section(s) 10–601(p) through (hhh) of Article – Economic Development of the
8 Annotated Code of Maryland be renumbered to be Section(s) 10–601(r) through (jjj),
9 respectively.
10 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That the Laws of Maryland read
11 as follows:
12 Article – Economic Development
13 10–601.
14 (P) “CARROLL PARK SOCCER STADIUM AND FACILITY” MEANS A SOCCER
15 STADIUM AND FACILITY LOCATED IN BALTIMORE CITY THAT IS USED PRIMARILY
16 FOR PROFESSIONAL SOCCER AND AS A SOCCER ACADEMY AND SCHOOL.
17 (Q) “CARROLL PARK SOCCER STADIUM AND FACILITY FUND” MEANS THE
18 CARROLL PARK SOCCER STADIUM AND FACILITY FUND ESTABLISHED UNDER §
19 10–657.7 OF THIS SUBTITLE.
20 (u) “Facility” means:
21 (1) a structure or other improvement developed at Camden Yards;
22 (2) a convention facility;
23 (3) the Hippodrome Performing Arts facility;
24 (4) a sports facility;
25 (5) a Baltimore City public school facility;
26 (6) a racing facility;
27 (7) a training facility for thoroughbred horses;
28 (8) a public school facility;
29 (9) the Hagerstown Multi–Use Sports and Events Facility;

4 HOUSE BILL 1078
1 (10) a sports entertainment facility; [or]
2 (11) a Prince George’s County Blue Line Corridor facility; OR
3 (12) THE CARROLL PARK SOCCER STADIUM AND FACILITY.
4 10–613.
5 (b) The Authority may review and make recommendations on proposed
6 convention center facilities, the Hippodrome Performing Arts facility, the Hagerstown
7 Multi–Use Sports and Events Facility, [and] a Prince George’s County Blue Line Corridor
8 facility, AND THE CARROLL PARK SOCCER STADIUM AND FACILITY, including the
9 expansion and enhancement of the Baltimore City Convention Center and the Ocean City
10 Convention Center and the development and construction of the Montgomery County
11 Conference Center, the Hippodrome Performing Arts Center, the Hagerstown Multi–Use
12 Sports and Events Facility, [and] a Prince George’s County Blue Line Corridor facility,
13 AND THE CARROLL PARK SOCCER STADIUM AND FACILITY with respect to location,
14 purpose, design, function, capacity, parking, costs, funding mechanisms, and revenue
15 alternatives, with specific recommendations on:
16 (1) the level of support from the private sector;
17 (2) the type of support from the private sector;
18 (3) special taxing sources;
19 (4) projected revenues;
20 (5) bonding authority and the source of debt service; and
21 (6) the fiscal impact on the State of any revenue alternatives.
22 10–618.
23 (b) The Authority may:
24 (1) acquire by any of the means specified in § 10–620(a) of this subtitle:
25 (i) a site at Camden Yards for a facility;
26 (ii) a Baltimore Convention site or an interest in the site;
27 (iii) an Ocean City Convention site or an interest in the site;
28 (iv) a Montgomery County Conference site or an interest in the site;

