3 10–628.
4 (c) (1) Unless authorized by the General Assembly, the Board of Public Works
5 may not approve an issuance by the Authority of bonds, whether taxable or tax exempt,
6 that constitute tax supported debt or nontax supported debt if, after issuance, there would
7 be outstanding and unpaid more than the following face amounts of the bonds for the
8 purpose of financing acquisition, construction, renovation, and related expenses for
9 construction management, professional fees, and contingencies in connection with:
10 (i) the Baltimore Convention facility – $55,000,000;
11 (ii) the Hippodrome Performing Arts facility – $20,250,000;
12 (iii) the Montgomery County Conference facility – $23,185,000;
13 (iv) the Ocean City Convention facility – $24,500,000;
14 (v) Baltimore City public school facilities – $1,100,000,000;
15 (vi) supplemental facilities – $25,000,000;
16 (vii) racing facilities – $400,000,000;
17 (viii) public school facilities in the State – $2,200,000,000;
18 (ix) the Hagerstown Multi–Use Sports and Events Facility –
19 $59,500,000;
20 (x) sports entertainment facilities – $220,000,000; [and]
21 (xi) Prince George’s County Blue Line Corridor facilities –
22 $400,000,000; AND
23 (XII) THE CARROLL PARK SOCCER STADIUM AND FACILITY –
24 $216,600,000.
25 10–634.
26 (a) A pledge by the Authority of revenues or money deposited in the Baltimore
27 City Public School Construction Financing Fund [or], the Supplemental Public School
28 Construction Financing Fund, OR THE CARROLL PARK SOCCER STADIUM AND

8 HOUSE BILL 1078
1 FACILITY FUND as security for an issue of bonds is valid and binding from when the pledge
2 is made.
3 (b) (1) The revenues or money deposited in the Baltimore City Public School
4 Construction Financing Fund [or], the Supplemental Public School Construction Financing
5 Fund, OR THE CARROLL PARK SOCCER STADIUM AND FACILITY FUND that are
6 pledged are immediately subject to the lien of the pledge without any physical delivery or
7 further act.
8 (2) The lien of any pledge is valid and binding against any person having a
9 claim against the Authority in tort, contract, or otherwise, regardless of whether the person
10 has notice of the lien.
11 (c) Notwithstanding any other provision of law, in order to perfect a lien on
12 pledged revenues or money deposited in the Baltimore City Public School Construction
13 Financing Fund [or], the Supplemental Public School Construction Financing Fund, OR
14 THE CARROLL PARK SOCCER STADIUM AND FACILITY FUND against a third person,
15 it is not necessary to file or record any document adopted or entered into by the Authority
16 in any public record other than in the records of the Authority.
17 10–646.5.
18 (A) EXCEPT AS AUTHORIZED BY § 10–639 OF THIS SUBTITLE, TO FINANCE
19 SITE ACQUISITION, DESIGN, AND CONSTRUCTION OF ANY SEGMENT OF THE
20 CARROLL PARK SOCCER STADIUM AND FACILITY, THE AUTHORITY SHALL COMPLY
21 WITH THIS SECTION.
22 (B) AT LEAST 45 DAYS BEFORE SEEKING APPROVAL OF THE BOARD OF
23 PUBLIC WORKS FOR EACH BOND ISSUE OR OTHER BORROWING, THE AUTHORITY
24 SHALL PROVIDE TO THE FISCAL COMMITTEES OF THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY, IN
25 ACCORDANCE WITH § 2–1257 OF THE STATE GOVERNMENT ARTICLE, A
26 COMPREHENSIVE FINANCING PLAN FOR THE RELEVANT SEGMENT OF THE FACILITY.
27 (C) THE AUTHORITY SHALL OBTAIN THE APPROVAL OF THE BOARD OF
28 PUBLIC WORKS OF THE PROPOSED BOND ISSUE AND THE FINANCING PLAN.
29 (D) FOR FISCAL YEAR 2028 AND EACH FISCAL YEAR THEREAFTER, UNTIL
30 THE BONDS THAT HAVE BEEN ISSUED TO FINANCE THE CARROLL PARK SOCCER
31 STADIUM AND FACILITY ARE NO LONGER OUTSTANDING AND UNPAID, THE
32 COMPTROLLER SHALL DEPOSIT INTO THE CARROLL PARK SOCCER STADIUM AND
33 FACILITY FUND THE AMOUNT NECESSARY TO PAY PRINCIPAL AND INTEREST ON THE
34 BONDS FOR THAT FISCAL YEAR AS REQUIRED UNDER § 9–1E–12(B)(2)(III) OF THE
35 STATE GOVERNMENT ARTICLE.

HOUSE BILL 1078 9
1 (E) THE AUTHORITY MAY NOT ISSUE BONDS TO FINANCE THE CARROLL
2 PARK SOCCER STADIUM AND FACILITY UNTIL THE AUTHORITY AND UNITED
3 PARTNERSHIP SECURE A WRITTEN OPERATING AGREEMENT.
4 10–657.7.
5 (A) IN THIS SECTION, “FUND” MEANS THE CARROLL PARK SOCCER
6 STADIUM AND FACILITY FUND.
7 (B) THERE IS A CARROLL PARK SOCCER STADIUM AND FACILITY FUND.
8 (C) THE PURPOSE OF THE FUND IS TO ENABLE THE AUTHORITY TO:
9 (1) USE THE FUND AS A REVOLVING FUND FOR IMPLEMENTING THIS
10 SUBTITLE AS IT RELATES TO THE CARROLL PARK SOCCER STADIUM AND FACILITY;
11 AND
12 (2) PAY ANY EXPENSES INCURRED BY THE AUTHORITY THAT ARE
13 RELATED TO THE CARROLL PARK SOCCER STADIUM AND FACILITY.
14 (D) THE AUTHORITY SHALL ADMINISTER THE FUND.
15 (E) (1) THE FUND IS A CONTINUING, NONLAPSING FUND THAT IS NOT
16 SUBJECT TO REVERSION UNDER § 7–302 OF THE STATE FINANCE AND
17 PROCUREMENT ARTICLE.
18 (2) THE STATE TREASURER SHALL HOLD THE FUND SEPARATELY,
19 AND THE COMPTROLLER SHALL ACCOUNT FOR THE FUND.
20 (F) (1) TO THE EXTENT CONSIDERED APPROPRIATE BY THE AUTHORITY,
21 THE RECEIPTS OF THE FUND SHALL BE PLEDGED TO AND CHARGED WITH THE
22 FOLLOWING RELATING TO THE CARROLL PARK SOCCER STADIUM AND FACILITY:
23 (I) PAYMENT OF DEBT SERVICE ON AUTHORITY BONDS;
24 (II) ALL REASONABLE CHARGES AND EXPENSES RELATED TO
25 THE AUTHORITY’S BORROWING; AND
26 (III) THE MANAGEMENT OF AUTHORITY OBLIGATIONS.
27 (2) THE PLEDGE SHALL BE EFFECTIVE AS PROVIDED IN § 10–634 OF
28 THIS SUBTITLE.
29 (G) THE FUND CONSISTS OF:

10 HOUSE BILL 1078
1 (1) MONEY APPROPRIATED FOR DEPOSIT IN THE FUND;
2 (2) REVENUES COLLECTED OR RECEIVED FROM ANY SOURCE UNDER
3 THIS SUBTITLE CONCERNING THE CARROLL PARK SOCCER STADIUM AND
4 FACILITY;
5 (3) INTEREST EARNINGS; AND
6 (4) ANY ADDITIONAL MONEY MADE AVAILABLE FROM ANY PUBLIC OR
7 PRIVATE SOURCE FOR THE PURPOSES ESTABLISHED FOR THE FUND.
8 (H) (1) THE STATE TREASURER SHALL INVEST THE MONEY OF THE FUND
9 IN THE SAME MANNER AS OTHER STATE MONEY MAY BE INVESTED.
10 (2) ANY INTEREST EARNINGS OF THE FUND SHALL BE PAID INTO THE
11 FUND.
